<subSubSection id="C31D6540FF9FBD13FA31FB68F90EFA3D" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BB836CBFF9FBD13FA31FB68F90EFA3D" blockId="3.[1458,2668,293,1590]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis id="B973EAD9FF9FBD13FA31FB68F881FB52" bold="true" box="[1462,1818,1239,1272]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List and the 2016 China Red List (under 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D48FF9FBD13F8D2FB41F877FAB5" authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1874" box="[1877,2028,1278,1311]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Siphneus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="psilurus">M. psilurus</taxonomicName>
in both). The Khingan Zokor is classified as “declining” in the Red Data Book of Russia (as 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D48FF9FBD13F7DCFA95F769FAED" authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1874" box="[2139,2290,1322,1351]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Siphneus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="psilurus">M. psilurus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C074D48FF9FBD13F77BFA95F6E3FAED" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1912" box="[2300,2424,1322,1351]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Myospalax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="epsilanus">epsilanus</taxonomicName>
). It is threatened by habitat degradation as natural landscapes are converted to agriculture. It occurs in protected areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
